Hi Michael,

Heritrix is up and running. Thank you very much for your assistance. I
really appreciate you hanging in with me on this...

This is what I had to do to get it running, not sure if all were required
steps but covered off on them anyway:

1. First, tried running Heritrix 1.4.0 with no luch.
2. Installed the most recent version of Java J2SE 5.0 Release 4
3. Checked Terminal, bash is supposedly default on Terminal for 10.2 and
higher, according to Apple, yet still had to set it in preferences,
restarted, etc., and relogged into OS X.
4. Tried wget command in Terminal, no response
5. Copied your indicated web address for Heritrix 1.9.0, downloaded via
Firefox, onto desktop, then moved to my home folder
6. Tried tar xfz command in Terminal, no response
6. Double-clicked .gz file to auto-untar and auto-ungzip
7. Doubleclicked on heritrix-1.9.0.jar -- error message
8. Typed cd heritrix-1.9.0-200606011911 in Terminal
9. Typed chmod u+x bin/heritrix
10.Typed .bin/heritrix

Mon Jun  5 12:41:24 EDT 2006 Starting heritrix....
Heritrix 1.9.0-200606011911 is running.

FYI the console log from below contained error messages after multiple
install and launch attempts

Now will try to replicate on desktop machine, a 2.1 ghz imac ppc w/1.5 gb
ram. Will post results as I can.

Thanks again, Michael, you are a Saint.

Rob Mothershead




